[http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] Our lovely yachting expert has stepped in with some more detail:

 &quot;One (vessel) is the same in both pics-  it’s the yacht with three portholes, I reckon the sail number is A3 from the second image, which means it is possibly KOALA, according to a list of SASC sail numbers in the early 1930s. It looks like an AC Barber design, it has his typical raised deck and rounded bow, but is perhaps a bit big to be one of his Prince Class designs which were very similar. It has a nice feature, an early version of a self-furling headsail, all the rage these days.&quot;

Nothing like having an expert handy :)
